            },
            "answer_text": "You can easily construct such a irrational number by specifying the sequence of digits. For example to exclude 9 we could construct 0.123456780123456780012345678000 etc This has the sequence 12345678 the first time followed by one zero, then by two zero's then three etc. Its easy enough to show the digit sequence never repeats so its not a rational number. I don't know if it turns out the be transcendental. ",
