                "name": "Kenneth Labuskes",
                "href": "/profile/Kenneth-Labuskes"
            },
            "answer_text": "Whether a number is irrational or not is not related to it's base.  For example, pi is irrational in any  base.   One characteristic of an irrational number is that its decimal representation does not terminate or repeat.  Using this rule, it is easy to create an irrational number that would  meet your requirements.  Examples: 0.23223222322223.....0.14114111411114...etc. ",
