            "answer_text": "For those interested in computability theory, you can say the following: All algebraic numbers are computable.  Therefore, all you need to do is pick your favorite uncomputable sequence of 0's and 1's.  The result will be an uncomputable (and non-algebraic) number whose decimal representation only contains 0's and 1's. For more info, see Alan Turing's paper on computable numbers.Link: http://www.turingarchive.org/browse.php/B/12Also see: Computable number ",
